<li id="cite_note-22"><b><a href="#cite_ref-22" title="">^</a></b> Timothy H. Goldsmith. "What Birds See", Scientific American, July 2006, Vol. 295, Issue 1.</li>
<li id="cite_note-23"><b><a href="#cite_ref-23" title="">^</a></b> FJ Varela, AG Palacios, and TM Goldsmith. "Vision, Brain, and Behavior in Birds", 1993. p. 77-94.</li>
<li id="cite_note-24"><b><a href="#cite_ref-24" title="">^</a></b> IC Cuthill, JC Partridge, ATD Bennett, SC Church, NS Hart, and S Hunt. “Ultraviolet Vision in Birds”. Advances in the Study of Behavior. 2000. Vol. 29: 159-214.</li>
<li id="cite_note-25"><b><a href="#cite_ref-25" title="">^</a></b> Ives, H.E. (1912) "The relation between the color of the illuminant and the color of the illuminated object." <i>Trans. Illuminat. Eng. Soc.</i> 7, 62–72, (Reprinted in: <i>Color Res. Appl.</i> 20, 70–75.).</li>
<li id="cite_note-26"><b><a href="#cite_ref-26" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFHannah_E._Smithson_and_Qasim_Zaidi2009">Hannah E. Smithson and Qasim Zaidi (2004). "<a href="http://www.journalofvision.org/4/9/3/article.aspx" class="external text" title="http://www.journalofvision.org/4/9/3/article.aspx" rel="nofollow">Colour constancy in context: Roles for local adaptation and levels of reference</a>". <i>Journal of Vision</i> <b>4</b> (9): 693–710. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1167%2F4.9.3" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1167%2F4.9.3" rel="nofollow">10.1167/4.9.3</a></span><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.journalofvision.org/4/9/3/article.aspx" class="external free" title="http://www.journalofvision.org/4/9/3/article.aspx" rel="nofollow">http://www.journalofvision.org/4/9/3/article.aspx</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Colour+constancy+in+context%3A+Roles+for+local+adaptation+and+levels+of+reference&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Vision&amp;rft.aulast=Hannah+E.+Smithson+and+Qasim+Zaidi&amp;rft.au=Hannah+E.+Smithson+and+Qasim+Zaidi&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.volume=4&amp;rft.issue=9&amp;rft.pages=693%E2%80%93710&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1167%2F4.9.3&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.journalofvision.org%2F4%2F9%2F3%2Farticle.aspx&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Color_vision"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-27"><b><a href="#cite_ref-27" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFHannah_E._Smithson2009">Hannah E. Smithson (2005). "<a href="http://journals.royalsociety.org/content/px26ma7w586vq2a7/" class="external text" title="http://journals.royalsociety.org/content/px26ma7w586vq2a7/" rel="nofollow">Review. Sensory, computational and cognitive components of human colour constancy</a>". <i>Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society</i> <b>360</b> (1458): 1329–1346. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1098%2Frstb.2005.1633" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1098%2Frstb.2005.1633" rel="nofollow">10.1098/rstb.2005.1633</a></span><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://journals.royalsociety.org/content/px26ma7w586vq2a7/" class="external free" title="http://journals.royalsociety.org/content/px26ma7w586vq2a7/" rel="nofollow">http://journals.royalsociety.org/content/px26ma7w586vq2a7/</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Review.+Sensory%2C+computational+and+cognitive+components+of+human+colour+constancy&amp;rft.jtitle=Philosophical+Transactions+of+the+Royal+Society&amp;rft.aulast=Hannah+E.+Smithson&amp;rft.au=Hannah+E.+Smithson&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.volume=360&amp;rft.issue=1458&amp;rft.pages=1329%E2%80%931346&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1098%2Frstb.2005.1633&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fjournals.royalsociety.org%2Fcontent%2Fpx26ma7w586vq2a7%2F&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Color_vision"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-28"><b><a href="#cite_ref-28" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFKarl_R._Gegenfurtner.2C_L._T._Sharpe1999">Karl R. Gegenfurtner, L. T. Sharpe (1999). <i><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=9R1ogJsPHi8C&amp;pg=PA413&amp;dq=von-kries+ives&amp;ei=gYuSR--JOZ6ktgOAkPVE&amp;ie=ISO-8859-1&amp;sig=9fSl-f7sE95QZ2mfBQSauPMhvrc" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=9R1ogJsPHi8C&amp;pg=PA413&amp;dq=von-kries+ives&amp;ei=gYuSR--JOZ6ktgOAkPVE&amp;ie=ISO-8859-1&amp;sig=9fSl-f7sE95QZ2mfBQSauPMhvrc" rel="nofollow">Color Vision: From Genes to Perception</a></i>. Cambridge University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/052100439X" class="internal">ISBN 052100439X</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=9R1ogJsPHi8C&amp;pg=PA413&amp;dq=von-kries+ives&amp;ei=gYuSR--JOZ6ktgOAkPVE&amp;ie=ISO-8859-1&amp;sig=9fSl-f7sE95QZ2mfBQSauPMhvrc" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=9R1ogJsPHi8C&amp;pg=PA413&amp;dq=von-kries+ives&amp;ei=gYuSR--JOZ6ktgOAkPVE&amp;ie=ISO-8859-1&amp;sig=9fSl-f7sE95QZ2mfBQSauPMhvrc" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=9R1ogJsPHi8C&amp;pg=PA413&amp;dq=von-kries+ives&amp;ei=gYuSR--JOZ6ktgOAkPVE&amp;ie=ISO-8859-1&amp;sig=9fSl-f7sE95QZ2mfBQSauPMhvrc</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Color+Vision%3A+From+Genes+to+Perception&amp;rft.aulast=Karl+R.+Gegenfurtner%2C+L.+T.+Sharpe&amp;rft.au=Karl+R.+Gegenfurtner%2C+L.+T.+Sharpe&amp;rft.date=1999&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=052100439X&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D9R1ogJsPHi8C%26pg%3DPA413%26dq%3Dvon-kries%2Bives%26ei%3DgYuSR--JOZ6ktgOAkPVE%26ie%3DISO-8859-1%26sig%3D9fSl-f7sE95QZ2mfBQSauPMhvrc&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Color_vision"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
